<div class="web-page">
    <div class="home-intro">
        <h1>Fantasiae Personae</h1>
        <p class="welcome">
            Welcome to Fantasiae Personae!
        </p>
        <p class="welcome">
            When reading a book, we often keep a specific image in our mind of how characters should look. Sometimes, this image can almost be amorphous and difficult to imagine.
        </p>
        <p class="welcome">
            This application seeks to help by providing you with images of the casts of actors starring in movies adapted from your chosen book and even allow you to create/view fancasts from other users!
        </p>
        <div>
            <h3>Get Started</h3>
            <h5>Search Book Adaptations by Title or Author</h5>
            <div class="search-container">
                <form action="/adaptations">
                  <input type="text" placeholder="Search.." name="book_search">
                  <button type="submit"><i class="fa fa-search"></i></button>
                </form>
            </div>
            <h5>Or Create Your Own Fancast for Your Favorite Novel</h5>
                <a href="/create-fancast"><button>Create</button></a>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="member-login">
        <h3>Member Sign In</h3>
        <form method="POST" action="https://cs361-auth-service.herokuapp.com/api/user/login/" id="home_login" onsubmit>
            <fieldset>
                <input type="hidden" name="next" value="/">
                <label for="home_username">Username</label>
                <input type="text" name="username" size="25" id="home_username" maxlength="30">
                <label for="home_password">Password</label>
                <input type="password" name="password" id="home_password" size="16" maxlength="30">
                <input type="submit" class="home-button" name="login" id="home_login_submit" value="Sign in">
                <h5>Don't have an account?</h5>
                <a id="register-link" href="/new-user-register">Create a free account now</a>
            </fieldset>
        </form>
    </div>
</div>
